label.value: immune epitope carrier role

definition.value: A role inhering in a material entity that is covalently bound to an epitope in order to increase the epitopes immunogenicity.

label.value: adjuvant role

definition.value: Adjuvant role is a role that inheres in a material entity and which is realized through a process of modifying a biological response.

label.value: disposition to infect an organism

definition.value: Is a role borne by an agent, and realized when in contact with or inside another organism in which it is capable of replicating and causing disease

label.value: immunization

definition.value: The process of an epitope that is part of or derived from an immunogen coming into contact with adaptive immune cells resulting in these cells acquiring immune effector functions specific for the epitope.

label.value: blood harvesting

definition.value: A material separation where blood is taken from an organism.

label.value: L cell line

definition.value: A cell line derived from mouse fibroblasts.

label.value: cultured antigen presenting cell population

definition.value: a cell culture including cells that have an antigen presentation function

label.value: cultured effector T cell population

definition.value: A cell culture including cells that have an effector T cell function

label.value: material to be added

definition.value: a material that is added to another one in a material combination process

label.value: target of material addition

definition.value: A material entity into which another is being added in a material combinatino process

label.value: environmental proximity to infectious agent

definition.value: Is a process in which an infectious agent comes close enough to a potential host organism in its habitat that a contact can result

label.value: contact to pathogen carrying biological vector

definition.value: a process in which a vector carrying an infectious agent comes close enough to a potential host organism that a contact can result

label.value: splenocyte specimen

definition.value: A cell specimen comprised of a mixed cell population obtained by processing whole spleen into individual cells, typically performed using a sieve or blender. This population includes T cells, B cells, macrophages, and other cell types.

label.value: P815 cell line

definition.value: A cell line derived from mouse mastocytoma.

label.value: assay antigen role

definition.value: Any molecule recognized by the adaptive immune receptors? Recognized means bound with a certain affinity? From GO ag binding:Interacting selectively with an antigen, any substance which is capable of inducing a specific immune response and of reacting with the products of that response, the specific antibody or specifically sensitized T-lymphocytes, or both. Binding may counteract the biological activity of the antigen. see OBI_1110120 below

label.value: pathologic process

definition.value: abnormal, harmful processes caused by or associated with a disease

label.value: assay measuring qualitiative binding of a T cell epitope:MHC:TCR complex

definition.value: A T cell epitope recognition assay that qualitatively detects MHC:epitope complex binding to TCR.

label.value: assay measuring MHC ligand processing and presentation

definition.value: A MHC ligand assay that determines what ligands are processed and loaded onto MHC molecules by eluting ligands and identifying them.

label.value: assay measuring binding of a MHC:ligand complex

definition.value: A MHC ligand assay that detects the binding of a ligand to an MHC molecule.

label.value: assay measuring binding of a B cell epitope:antibody complex

definition.value: An immune epitope assay that detects B cell epitope recognition.

label.value: immune epitope assay

definition.value: An assay that detects the binding of an epitope to an adaptive immune receptor or a immune response process resulting from such a binding event

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific cytokine production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope dependent biological activity assay that detects cytokine production.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific T cell killing

definition.value: A T cell epitope dependent biological activity assay that detects the killing of an antigen presenting cell (APC) by a T cell whose TCR recognizes an epitope presented by the APC.

definition.value: A T cell epitope dependent biological activity assay that detects T cell proliferation.

label.value: CD8 receptor

definition.value: A transmembrane glycoprotein that serves as a co-receptor for the T cell receptor.
